<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-27T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-27T11:29:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1148</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T11:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Delayed radio from Guantanamo Naval Station just received says expected
                            to land two hundred men midnight Sunday in Guantanamo town, as
                            systematic destruction cane had commenced and disorder and danger to
                            life threatened.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>